 The State Government of Tamil Nadu cannot keep any adolescent offender who is convicted of a capital offence but sentenced to imprisonment of life in respect of whom an order is made under section 10-A of the Tamil Nadu Borstal Schools Act in a Borstal School or in any other kind of detention after he has attained 23 years of age The State Government is therefore directed to release forthwith all such inmates of the Borstal Schools in Tamil Nadu who have attained 23 years of age. [1058E-F] State of Andhra Pradesh v. Vallabhapuram Ravi [1996] INSC 180; [1984] 2 SCALE 386, followed.
 In re. Ganapati, 1983 Criminal Law Journal 509, over- ruled.
